<section id="fs-idp61186848" class="summary">
<title>Key Concepts and Summary</title>
<para id="fs-idp166596960">The addition of nitrogen into an organic framework leads to two families of molecules. Compounds containing a nitrogen atom bonded in a hydrocarbon framework are classified as amines. Compounds that have a nitrogen atom bonded to one side of a carbonyl group are classified as amides. Amines are a basic functional group. Amines and carboxylic acids can combine in a condensation reaction to form amides.</para>
</section>
